    <!-- <p>This page will be built out later on, but for now it'll just have an input that lets you see whether a channel has goby set up, and sends you to the appropriate page from there</p> -->

    <article class="prose centered">
      <h1 >Are.na + Goby</h1>
      <h2>Enter a channel URL to get started:</h2>
      <div class="flex-row input-url" id="channel-search">
        <input type="text" name="" value="" placeholder="https://are.na/<username-slug>/<channel-slug>">
        <button type="button" name="button" id="initiate-search">Go</button>
      </div>
      <!-- <h2>About Goby</h2> -->
      <p>Hi, thanks for stopping by!</p>
      <p>Goby is a tool for enriching <a href="https://are.na/" target="_blank">Are.na</a> channels with custom metadata.</p>
      <p>It lets you add/organize new fields for your blocks with different types of information:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><svg class="inline form-edit" width="24" height="22"><use href="#string-icon"></svg> Short text strings</li>
        <li><svg class="inline form-edit" width="24" height="22"><use href="#par-icon"></svg> Longform text w/ markdown</li>
        <li><svg class="inline form-edit" width="24" height="22"><use href="#url-icon"></svg> URLs</li>
        <li><svg class="inline form-edit" width="24" height="22"><use href="#array-icon"></svg> Tags</li>
      </ul>
      <p>I'll eventually explain in more detail here, but for now you can check out <a href="https://www.are.na/nico-chilla/goby-journal">this channel</a> and the <a href="https://github.com/nchilla/goby">github repo</a> to learn more about the project.</p>
      <p>â€” Nico <a target="_blank" href="https://www.are.na/nico-chilla/"><svg class="inline form-edit" width="24" height="22"><use href="#arena-icon"></svg></a></p>
    </article>
